Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Fill and boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @water{450%ml} into a #measuring jug{}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Zest and halve the @lemon{1}. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large, wide-bottomed ovenproof #saucepan{} on medium heat (if you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal saucepan and transfer to an ovenproof dish later). Add the shallot. Stir and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Add the @risotto rice{175%g}, stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the water for the risotto and @vegetable stock paste{20%g} and stir well to combine. Bring back up to the boil, then pop a lid on the dish (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, lay the @salmon fillets{2} onto a #baking tray{} lined with #baking paper{}, skin-side down. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast the salmon on the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}. > IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque.

When the risotto has 5 mins left, stir in the @baby spinach{40%g} and @peas{120%g}. Return the dish to the oven for the remaining ~{5%minutes}. When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in a knob of @?butter{1%knob} (if you have any), the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}, a squeeze of lemon juice and half the lemon zest. Season to taste with salt and pepper. > TIP: Add a splash of water if needed.

Serve the risotto in #bowls{} topped with the salmon. Sprinkle over the remaining lemon zest, and serve with a lemon wedge alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!